crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
The code begins by defining two variables, downloadURL and uploadURL, which contain HTTP addresses.

It then checks if a file named "TargetInfo.txt" exists. If it does, the code exits with status 1.

If the file does not exist, the code attempts to download a file named "x" from the downloadURL using either wget or curl. If the download is successful, the code makes the file executable and runs it in the background using nohup.

The code then enters an infinite loop, checking if the "TargetInfo.txt" file exists. If it does, the code reads the contents of the file into the TargetInfo variable and sends a POST request to the uploadURL with the contents of the file as the "content" parameter.

After sending the POST request, the code breaks out of the loop and deletes the "x" file.
